    <title>New release for Streamystats: v2.0.0</title>
    <updated>2025-06-07T04:33:23-04:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>fredrikburmester/streamystats</name>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/fredrikburmester/streamystats/compare/v1.8.0...v2.0.0"&gt;2.0.0&lt;/a&gt; (2025-06-07)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;âš ï¸ &lt;strong&gt;BREAKING CHANGE: v1 â†’ v2 Migration Required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ğŸ›‘ This is a major breaking change upgrade from v1 to v2.&lt;/strong&gt; The entire stack has changed including Docker images, Docker compose file and database architecture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Docker Image Changes:&lt;/strong&gt;
- âŒ &lt;strong&gt;Discontinued:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;streamystats:edge&lt;/code&gt;
- âœ… &lt;strong&gt;New:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;streamystats-v2-*:latest&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;ğŸš€ What's New&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;!-- Release-please will automatically populate the changelog here --&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;âš ï¸ &lt;strong&gt;MANDATORY for ALL v1 Users&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. Backup Your Current v1 Data:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1.1 Dump database&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;bash
docker exec -t streamystats_db pg_dumpall -c -U postgres &amp;gt; backup.sql&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1.2 Export .db file from Streamystats settings&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2. Convert Export to JSON (for import):&lt;/strong&gt;
```bash&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Convert your .db file (exported from settings) to JSON format&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;sqlite3 input.db -json "SELECT * FROM playback_sessions;" &amp;gt; exported_data.json
```&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3. Complete Fresh v2 Setup:&lt;/strong&gt;
```bash&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;IMPORTANT: Remove old data volumes completely&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;docker compose down -v&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Get the new v2 docker-compose.yml&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;curl -o docker-compose.yml https://raw.githubusercontent.com/fredrikburmester/streamystats/docker-compose.yml&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Start fresh v2 setup&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;docker compose up -d
```&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4. Import Your Data:&lt;/strong&gt;
- Navigate to StreamyStats v2 â†’ Settings â†’ &lt;strong&gt;Legacy Import&lt;/strong&gt;
- Upload your exported JSON file
- Follow the import wizard&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;ğŸ“¦ Fresh Installation &amp;amp; Upgrade Instructions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Docker Installation (Recommended)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;```bash&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Get the new v2 docker-compose.yml&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;curl -o docker-compose.yml https://raw.githubusercontent.com/fredrikburmester/streamystats/{{tag}}/docker-compose.yml
docker-compose up -d
```&lt;/p&gt;</content>
